          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "IOCH"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A gaseous ionization detector of the parallel",
                " plate avalanche detector (PPAD)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The targets  were  thin films deposited on the plates",
                " of PPAD.  In the  case  of  uranium  there  were  26",
                " Deposits  of (U-238(O-2)) with total thickness about",
                " 52 mg/cm**2 and 30  deposits  of  (U-235(O-2))  with",
                " total  thickness  about 62 mg/cm**2.  In the case oF",
                " thorium there were 58  deposits  of  (Th(0-2))  with",
                " total thickness about 122 mg/cm**2."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "PART-DET": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "FF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Direct measurements   of  cross  section  values  for",
                " coincidence counts between the tagged electrons from",
                " linac  and  the fission detector taking into account",
                " such  quantities  as  efficiency  of   tagging   and",
                " equivalent thickness of the target."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The absolute photofission cross sections  for  Th-232",
                " and  U-235,238  have been studied from 20 to 110 MeV",
                " using the photon tagging  technique  at  the  Saclay",
                " linear   electron  accelerator  (ALS).  The  fission",
                " fragments were directly detected  using  a  parallel",
                " plate   avalanche   detector   (PPAD).   The   basic",
                " experimental results are  the  set  of  data  giving",
                " sigma(Eg,fission).  From a comparison of the present",
                " fission  data  with  the  total   absorption   cross",
                " sections   the   total  fission  probabilities  were",
                " deduced."
              ]
            }
          ],
